Job Title:     Director, Sr. HR Business Partner
Job Location:  PA: Wayne
Pay Rate:      competitive
Job Length:    full time
Start Date:    2007-11-18

Company Name:  Shire Pharmaceuticals, Inc.
Contact:       Human Resources
Phone:         email only
Fax:           email only

Description:   Develops, plans and directs the delivery of HR programs and services to selected business/functional groups (on a global basis if applicable).  Supports business strategy and objectives through people management expertise.  Works strategically and in partnership with the business to develop and implement focused workforce strategy.  Utilizes extensive knowledge of the business and HR to drive programs for recruiting, developing and retaining the best employees worldwide; leading organizational change and design; managing culture and maintaining a positive, highly productive work environment.  Forms effective relationships with the business and is viewed as the go-to person by management and employees.  Maintains extensive understanding of business objectives and operating environment to be able to deliver applicable solutions. Coordinates and works as part of a team with other HR colleagues to ensure consistency of process and policy application. Ensures business interests are represented in the design of HR programs.  Manages team of HR manager(s) and professionals to deliver the above.  Serves as member of HR senior management team and the senior management team of the business/functional groups supported.

Partner with assigned business/functional group(s) to provide consultation, workforce strategy development, and the delivery of HR programs and services to the group(s).  Represent the interests of the group(s) to the HR group.
Act as primary point of contact for members of the group(s).
Drive programs for recruiting, developing and retaining the best employees worldwide; Coordinate and engage in recruitment and selection activities for the group(s), including coordination of relocation, expatriation and immigration.  Manage the posting of internal and external job postings for Groups supported.
Lead organizational change and design for Groups supported by working proactively with senior management and HR specialists to identify operating, process, and workforce requirements and implement appropriate solutions.  Drive corporate change initiatives through to the business.
Maintain thorough understanding of key activities and issues with other functions/groups and collaborate with other Sr HR BPs to ensure organizational communication, and enable success of cross-functional efforts
Deliver program in support organizational team orientation and corporate values.  Deliver programs for managing culture and maintaining a positive, highly productive work environment.  Collaborate with other HR BPs and HR specialists.
Provide a range of employee relations services and support to the group(s).
Work with managers and employees in defining and following through with objectives, actions, and behaviors that enable the achievement of the Group(s) objectives.
Provide management information and trend data to the group(s).
Provide basic support to the business for compensation and benefit issues.
Work with HR specialists and the entire HR team to deliver customized programs and services to the business in the areas of compensation, competitive information/practices, employee relations, staffing, organizational development, learning and performance management, and data management and reporting.
Provide leadership to direct reports and serve as mentor to other more junior HR staff, developing them and providing general guidance.  Ensure the development and implementation of individual objectives, development plans and career plans for subordinates.
Manage salary survey process for the groups.
Plan and implement human resources projects and programs as assigned.
May act as Team Member or Team Leader on various HR or business project teams locally or globally.
Requirements:
Bachelors Degree or equivalent.
MBA preferred.
Minimum of ten years experience in a generalist, recruitment, and employee relations function.
Minimum 5 years in a senior HR leadership capacity.
Progressive HR experience as a strategic business partner; experience related to the specific business unit (Business Development, Finance, IT) highly preferred
Business acumen, business management and the ability to understand business strategy.
Strong interpersonal and communication skills and the ability to work effectively with all levels of staff.
Team player; natural collaborator yet able to take stance on tough/contentious issues.
Strong customer service orientation
Strong negotiation and influencing skills.
Problem solving, negotiation, and people management skills.
Communication, influence and relationship-building skills: ability to communicate effectively, both verbally and in writing. Knowledge of employee relations principles, practices, methods, and programs.
Knowledge and understanding of federal and state employment and labor laws, regulations, procedures, and standards.
Knowledge of a range of dispute resolution techniques.
Ability to develop and present educational programs and/or workshops.
Ability to make administrative and procedural decisions and judgments on sensitive, confidential issues.
Ability to foster a cooperative environment.
Team-orientation and collaboration.
Demonstrated ability to source, interview, and select candidates.
Ability to travel within the US but also internationally as necessary.
Minimum Experience:  10 years

